headline: TSMC Stock Rises Despite Sales Growth Slowdown. Why the AI Trade Is Alive and Well.
summary: Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing  just reported its slowest rate of monthly sales growth in more than 18 months.  TSMC reported October revenue of 367.47 billion New Taiwan dollars ($11.86 billion).  While that’s a new monthly record for the Taiwanese chip manufacturer, the 17% growth from the same month last year is the slowest pace of annual growth TSMC has registered since February 2024.
